$$

If $a=\frac{-x \pm \sqrt{28-3 x^{2}}}{2\left(x^{2}-7\right)}$,
$\therefore$ when $x=1$, $a=\frac{1}{2}$ or $-\frac{1}{3}$;
when $x=-1$, $a=\frac{1}{3}$ or $-\frac{1}{2}$;
when $x=2$, $a=1$ or $-\frac{1}{3}$;
when $x=-2$, $a=\frac{1}{3}$ or $-1$;
when $x=3$, $a=-\frac{1}{2}$ or $-1$;
when $x=-3$, $a=\frac{1}{2}$ or $1$;
when $x=0$, $a=\frac{\sqrt{7}}{7}$ or $-\frac{\sqrt{7}}{7}$.
When $a>0$ and $a=1$, $x=2$ or -3; when $a=\frac{1}{2}$, $x=1$ or -3;
when $a=\frac{1}{3}$, $x=-2$ or -1;

Therefore, the sum of the values of $a$ is $1+\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{3}=\frac{11}{6}$.

