- the notion of an even, odd, or periodic function;
- the notion of a bounded or constant function;
- the use of induction to calculate integer values of our function;
- the Cauchy equation
- the fact that some variables play symmetric roles in the equation or only in certain terms of the equation;
- more generally, the fact that certain transformations on the variables leave a term of the equation unchanged (or almost unchanged);
- the importance of handling small cases: taking variables equal to 0, 1, or -1, or even equal to each other, ...
- the search for roots or fixed points, that is, numbers $x$ such that $f(x)=0$ or $f(x)=x$
- the fact of considering an antecedent of a given value, or even a variable whose image is minimal or maximal, ...

