Notice that $\left(a^{2}+3 a b+3 b^{2}-1\right) \mid(a+b)^{3}$, and $(a+b)^{3}$ is a perfect cube, hence
$$
\begin{array}{l}
\prod_{i=1}^{n} p_{i}^{3} \mid(a+b)^{3} \\
\Rightarrow(a+b)^{3} \geq \prod_{i=1}^{n} p_{i}^{3}
\end{array}
$$

Thus we know
$$
(a+b)^{2} \geq \prod_{i=1}^{n} p_{i}^{2} \geq \prod_{i=1}^{n} p_{i}^{\alpha_{i}}=a^{2}+3 a b+3 b^{2}-1>(a+b)^{2}
$$

This leads to a contradiction.
In conclusion, the proposition is proved!

